AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 6001* House Bill No. 6004
by deleting subdivision (4) of § 49-6-3502 in Section 2 and substituting:
(4) "Private school" means a school that is:
(A) Located in this state;
(B) A private school, as defined in § 49-6-3001(c)(3)(A)(iii), that is a
category I, II, or III school approved by the commissioner of education in
accordance with rules promulgated by the state board of education; and
(C) Applies to be approved by the department in accordance with § 49-6-
3503;
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting "49-6-3503. Creation." in Section 2 and substituting "49-
6-3503. Creation - Private school requirements." and adding the following as a new
subsection to the end of the amendatory language in § 49-6-3503 of Section 2:
(c) The department shall:
(1) Administer an approval process for a private school, as defined in §
49-6-3001(c)(3)(A)(iii), to be eligible to enroll recipients;
(2) Create an application form that a private school, as defined in § 49-6-
3001(c)(3)(A)(iii), may submit to the department for approval to be eligible to
enroll recipients; and
(3) Approve applicants that:
(A) Demonstrate financial solvency; and
(B) Have been in operation and serving students in this state for
at least five (5) years.
